About Me

I am currently a Phd student in Management and Industrial engineering at Sapienza University of Rome with a focus on performance and data analysis.
I work also in ETL, Data Analysis, Text Mining, Data visualization and infographics, etc...
I don't think there's a position for the jobs I've done in the past...
let's just say I do a little bit of everything in the data environment.

What I’m good at?

I have a lot of experience with programming (I have been programming for almost 10 years) and I have worked with various languages, from classic object-oriented to functional programming.
Although I am an analytical, I have also worked a lot with graphics and design of both images and videos.

Data Analysis

Doing research, data analysis is my main activity. I'm specialized in statistical and performance analysis. The main methodologies I am familiar with are non-parametric and stochastic. In particular, I have experience with SFA and DEA analysis and, although to a lesser extent, MCDM as well. Lately I've been getting into ML (especially xgboost, svm and random forest) and text analysis(NRC sentiment dictionary and syuzhet analysis).

SQL, ETL and DB design

I've experience with classic SQL and the various CRUD operations.
In addition, thanks to the last years of experience as a researcher, I often work in the ETL processes.
Always in the context of data, I have experience in the design and implementation of databases from scratch.

Software Development

I've been developing since I was 16 in lots of languages.
For the past few years I've been working primarily in C#/.NET and R.
Most of my softwares are self-produced and are often in support of my research.

Data Visualization

Data visualization has become my greatest passion over time. I often create charts, infographics and interactive dashboards both numerical and geospatial.
I have made my motto: "better an ugly chart than 10 tables".
